NOTE: COMPLETE CLOUDFLARE WORKER STATIC SITE SETUP
ARCHITECT: ANDREI SARTE
DOMAIN MODEL: SOVEREIGN WORKER ENGINE
REQUIREMENTS: NO PAGES, NO KV, WORKER-ONLY SITE HOSTING

==============================
1. WORKER STRUCTURE
==============================

worker.js
/static/index.html
/static/style.css
/static/script.js

Cloudflare will bundle these automatically.

==============================
2. WORKER CODE (COPY EXACTLY)
==============================

export default {
  async fetch(request) {
    const url = new URL(request.url);
    let path = url.pathname;

    // Default root
    if (path === "/") path = "/index.html";

    try {
      const asset = await import(`./static${path}`);

      return new Response(asset.default, {
        headers: { "content-type": getType(path) }
      });

    } catch (err) {
      return new Response("Asset not found: " + path, { status: 404 });
    }
  }
};

function getType(path) {
  if (path.endsWith(".html")) return "text/html; charset=UTF-8";
  if (path.endsWith(".css")) return "text/css";
  if (path.endsWith(".js")) return "application/javascript";
  return "text/plain";
}

==============================
3. WHAT THIS WORKER DOES
==============================

• Serves index.html directly from the Worker bundle.
• Serves CSS and JS directly.
• Requires NO KV.
• Requires NO Pages.
• Requires NO build pipeline.
• Replaces your entire web server with one Worker.
• Sovereign behavior: YOU control all files.

==============================
4. ROUTE REQUIRED
==============================

andreisarte.com/*

==============================
5. DEPLOYMENT STEPS
==============================

(1) Create Worker
(2) Add the file structure:
    /worker.js
    /static/index.html
    /static/style.css
    /static/script.js
(3) Paste Worker code into worker.js
(4) Add route: andreisarte.com/*
(5) Deploy

==============================
6. RESULT
==============================

• Your site runs entirely on the Worker.
• Zero dependence on Cloudflare Pages.
• Zero proxy issues.
• Zero asset errors.
• Total domain sovereignty.
• Fully portable to ANY domain you choose.

